result.execSummary:
The defendant Gordon W. Kemmer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called @ 2:44 p.m. Defendant Gordon W. Kemmer in court with attorney Jeffrey Thomas Haase.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Upon motion of the State the Court amends Ct 1 to Misdemeanor Possession of THC contrary to Wis Stat 961.41(3g)(e). Plea: Ct 1 & 3 - NC.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Ct 2 - DRI.  Uncharged referral for Disorderly Conduct with an offense date of 8/12/2014 - DRI. Statement by Atty Haase regarding sentencing - requesting early termination. Statement by ADA Anderson regarding sentencing - objects to early termination of probation. No statement by DE. Court orders: S/W - 2 years probation - Conditions: NC w/ T. Truax, AODA and follow through, defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician,  Costs to include the DNA surcharge w/ 60 DTP or PP. The court does not allow for early termination of probation. Appeal rights given.
